name: Tour de cochon pour les marsus !

description: Just when Deadpool and Queen Shiklah think they've caught a break...THEN STRIKES M.O.D.O.K.*! (*Mighty Old Dude...Ostensibly...Kitzchy...?) The big-headed baddie has our heroes in his tiny little clutches as Deadpool's first Infinite Comic hits it midpoint!
name: Chapter 7: Ready? A.I.M. FIRE!
The Seekers ; The Hands from Nowhere!

volume.name: No Need for Tenchi! Part Three

description:
From the sands of the ages and halls of higher learning comes one of Batman’s deadliest foes – King Tut! Tut returns to Gotham City to assert his royal status and challenge the Dynamic Duo with his most far reaching plan yet to rule the modern Thebes known as Gotham City!

With a back-up story featuring Shame!

DIGITAL FIRST!
name: King Tut Barges In

description: When Starfire signs the team up for the popular reality show contest, I’ve Got Your Talent Right Here, Robin becomes determined to show the world just how talented the Teen Titans really are! Then, after a fight with Captain Cold, Beast Boy and Robin come down with a cold themselves! Running high fevers and quarantined from the rest of the Titans...the madness begins to set in!
name: Idol Hands

description: The Omega Company is on its last legs, but fights on! Amelia must confront The Magistrate, and put her burgeoning career as The Protector on the line! Exploding from the events of the Hidden War, It's Amelia Cole issue 13 -- AMELIA COLE and THE ENEMY UNLEASHED part 1!

volume.name: Amelia Cole and the Enemy Unleashed

description: Maya Diaz and her "pet" white gorilla, George Harrison, run a retrieval company: GoGetters Retrieval, Inc. Need something retrieved, be it a person, rare coin, a favorite cocktail jacket, or genetically engineered clown-panda? You call them. Hired to retrieve the only legal Double Eagle coin in existence, Maya and George find themselves fighting numerically challenged thugs and hoping they have enough nectarines to see them through.
With Kinski lost in a seemingly endless RV park, Joe must track down the puppy before he incurs the wrath of the locals.

volume.name: Craig Yoe's Weird but True Toon Factoids

description:
Atlantis is the world superpower, and Redum Anshargal is its worst enemy. If you want to break free of the system, he can offer you a place at his side, exploring the wild surface world in his watertight city barge The Deliverer. He and his hostage-protege Ukinnu Alal hunt the Amphibian, a legend that could be the key to an air-breathing life on land. But as they become the hunted, can Anshargal's team survive long enough to turn the tables on the godlike beast they set out for?

A brand new pulp monster adventure with Ray Harryhausen at its heart and a look at Atlantis like never before from the up-and-coming team of writer STEVE ORLANDO (Mystery in Space) and artist ARTYOM TRAKHANOV.

description:
After Thor's return to the pantheon of the biggest Marvel-Heroes become the God of Thunder and the mortal doctor Dr. Donald Blake one again. Together they have to deal with the mythic realm Asgard and the resurrection of its immortal gods - yet in a world, that maybe doesn't want them back!

Collects: Thor V3 #1 - 6

Release Dates

  • Austria: October 15, 2013
  • Germany: February 27, 2013
name: Vol. 52 - Thor - Die Rückkehr des Donners

deck: This issue marks the beginning of our first big adventure! We catch up with the three heroes as they find a blazing village.
description:
Over the Hills and Far Away

Our heroes face destruction as they begin to uncover an evil lurking in the shadows.
name: Over the Hills and Far Away

person_credits.name: Rick Troula
person_credits.role: writer, artist, penciler, letterer, colorist, cover

description:
In a city, where inflamed heroes fly in the sky, colorfully dressed manhunters climb up walls, silver skinned aliens promise the end of the world. We follow the experiences of a normal human, who witnesses the beginnings of the Marvel-Universe. Return to the first days of the Heroic Age and discover a world full of Marvels.

Collects: Marvels #0 - 4
name: Vol. 12 - Marvels

description:
Chapter 2 of 8. It's the end of the school year in 1998. Mark McGwire is racing Sammy Sosa to break the home run record, Bill Clinton is being questioned about a White House intern named Monica Lewinsky, Semisonic's Closing Time is on top of the charts, and Carl Carter is leading the Elizabeth Monarchs of rural Vermont to the state championship in his senior year. A full scholarship to the University of Maine is waiting for him, and everyone says he has a shot at the pros. He's so good he can do whatever he wants.

Until he makes one very arrogant mistake.
name: Chapter Two

description: In the year 2086 humanity faces a new threat, Extra Humans. The government is struggling to cope with the growing number of mutants, aliens and supernatural beings who are living amongst us. People are beginning to panic and so, in 2050, the Department for Extra Human Affairs was established with a remit to try and contain the problem. By 2086 the situation has escalated, so they have formed a new rapid response strike force, the Alpha Gods. Who better to police the Extra Human community than Extra Humans themselves? Paladin experiences a crisis of command which brings him closer to Impact. The Alpha Gods stage an assault on the safe house where Agent Omega is hiding, intending to put him down for good. However, all is not as it seems...at last the shocking identity of Agent Omega and the truth about Paladin is revealed!
name: Chapter Five: Don't Pray For Me

description: In the third and final installment of the Anne Steelyard series, A Thousand Waters, we find Anne still traveling across the desert with the help of Lady Hester's caravan and her friends. As Anne continues her search for the elusive City of Miyah, she discovers something utterly sinister and evil that makes her question everything and question who is worthy of her trust. With danger and duplicity surrounding her, Anne does whatever it takes to protect her country and to stop the Germans from establishing their secret base. Anne also believes this perilous path will secure the key to her freedom.
name: Act III: A Thousand Waters

volume.name: Anne Steelyard: The Garden of Emptiness

description: Excited for a new Betty & Veronica story? How about FOUR new B & V tales? First, in "The Minds of Betty and Veronica," we get an inside look at what the two BFFs REALLY think of each other -- and their thoughts may surprise you! Then in "The Wish," find out what happens when Betty FINALLY gets Archie all to herself! Next in "The Shopping Scene," can Veronica turn her shopping haul into profit? This time her spending spree may just help Daddykins' wallet! Finally, in "The Winning Float," it's girls vs. boys! Find out if the gals of Riverdale have what it takes to make the best float at the Homecoming game!
name: The Minds of Betty & Veronica; The Wish; The Shopping Scene; The Winning Float

description: After clashing with the "Roswell" gang, Bo lies in a coma. Now it's up to his posse to help him fight back from limbo to finish the job of taking out the next big boss, Serpent (a.k.a. Puppet Master).
name: Part 1

description: And once again, greetings dear potential buyer! And yes, It's still The Cartoon Guidebook To Absolute Failure. Written by Erik Craddock, and Illustrated by Logan Faerber. In this sixth and final heart-stopping issue, learn how easy it is to fail at classic time-tested outings such as: Interstellar Space travel, Winning the Lottery, Being Santa Claus, and so, so, SO much more!
name: Slasher Films, Deep Sea Exploration, and The Luge!

volume.name: The Cartoon Guidebook to Absolute Failure

description: Charlie has made some powerful friends in prison--but perhaps some even more powerful enemies.
Dan is out of air. Joules will kill him if he makes it out of this.

The national competition is coming up fast, and Julie, Lucie, and Alia will need all their skills, all their poise, and a lot of grit and determination to get their routine in perfect shape. The always jealous, ever-scheming Carla is trying to sabotage everything again, but the girls are used to that; what they weren't expecting was their teacher, Mary, falling sick at the worst possible moment! As they struggle to choreograph something on their own for the first time, it may be up to Lucie to step up and save the day.

Note: The digital edition (2/19/2014) for this volume was released before the print edition.
name: School Night Fever

description:
The third volume in the epic, six-volume saga created by one of the most unique visionaries in the history of the graphic novel!

Feuding, immortal cyborg gods; post apocalyptic worlds of bizarre and horrific mutations; hidden histories and secret kings; a story millennia in the telling... all that barely brushes the surface of this stunning series!

Newly restored art and lettering!

Exclusive all-new interviews and special features!

Note: The digital edition (2/19/2014) for this volume was released before the print edition.
name: Vengeance

description:
In the wake of an assault on Avenger's apartment, the heir to legendary supervillain Doctor Ex-Mortis is now loose and in charge of a superfortress/weapon in Earth's orbit! Aided by an Agency Zero veteran and an other-dimensional spell-caster, Britanny and Gina have to match wits with an unparalleled evil genius before he bends Kia to his ruthless will!

Note: The digital edition (2/19/2014) for this issue was released before the print edition.

As the world tries to make sense of The Healing and its consequences, an alcoholic makes plans to make the most of his second chance, a pharmaceutical exec and her assistant try to discover the limits of "The Healing" and the government starts planning their response.
Another warning from the dead. Plagued with bizarre visions, Sully's investigation begins to lead him towards the abyss.
Lord has put the call out and Brand is going to respond......in the most brutal way he can!

From the Shuster award winning creators of Least I Could Do and Gutters comes a loving nod to classic fantasy novels that manages to flip the genre on it's head. Unlikely heros cut a swath through a fantasy world that is extremely familiar and yet very different. A naive elven hunter makes an strange friend in an undead warlock and the two manage to make both enemies and friends as they fight the good fight against the Legaran Empire.

Down the rabbit hole they went leaving their high school behind and arriving at the strange capital of Akkades.

Now the Lost Kids must figure out what the heck is going on and why does everyone think Kate Beaux is a Princess here?

This is it! The issue every Mega-fan has been demanding! The debut of MEGA MAN X! But first, in "Shadow of the Moon" Part One: Mega Man joins a research team seeking the truth behind Dr. Wily and Ra Moon. But how far will they get when Shadow Man goes on the attack?! Then, in "The X Factor" Part One -- jump 100 years into the future as Dr. Cain discovers Dr. Light's final, greatest creation -- Mega Man X! Featuring pencils by the returning Mega Man art legend PATRICK "SPAZ" SPAZIANTE! The road to the next big mega-crossover starts here!

name: Shadow of Ra Moon Part One: Wayward Son; The X-Factor Part 1

description: Mall's on fire! Time for a costume change and some supering! But is this ninja looking guy and this sleepy looking guy too much for King Nilus and Everywhere Kid to handle on their own? And hey! Sergio! Stop touching things in your vampire uncle's creepy looking library! That's probably not a good idea!

Power hungry Shinobi Sun cooks up a plan with Medusa to work toward his ultimate goal: succession to lordship! He needs Gene to cooperate with his plan, but submitting to his demands means that Gene will be forced to give up the man he loves. Will he be able to resist Shinobi's methods of persuasion?

Meanwhile, Saul finds himself falling for Gene, who has recently been transformed into a vampire -- and a woman! Desperate to have the strength to protect his lady love, Saul seeks to make a deal with Aria -- but the exchange turns out to be more than he bargained for...
name: Vol. 10

description: The government has seized Liza's kids. Her friend is in danger. She's hundreds of miles from home and without powers. Is this the end?

Slaying the vampires who killed his father was only the beginning... the undead hordes are back, and more dangerous than ever. Fortunately, Pinocchio's not alone: in this thrilling sequel you'll meet his brothers and sisters from the famous Great Puppet Theater! Higgins and Jensen present a captivating blend of comedy, horror, romance, and high-seas adventure, rooted in the original Italian novel but brought - as if by magic - to new life.
name: The Great Puppet Theater

description: Still on their boat, they group has stopped to catch some dinner, but almost become dinner themselves. Luckily, they find an island. Now all they gotta do is survive the dangerous creatures that inhabit that island.
name: Chapter Three

description: While travelling on a somber mission to bury his recently deceased son, legendary hero Allan Quatermain is forced to confront both inner demons...and bestial undead ones too. When the body of his son disappears, he jumps headlong on a quest to reclaim the body and unburies several secrets some believe best left hidden. Woven into historical landscape of the brutal Belgian rule of the Congo, this new Quatermain adventure travels into the heart of darkness and remains true to the exploratory spirit of the original HR Haggard novels.
"HenShinHero": Meet the Veuniverse's only true purveyor of justice, Henshinhero, in this sweet homage to classic manga. Also features a collection of fantastic character pin-ups!
name: Henshinhero

description: It's a special super-sized edition of the Sonic Super digest! Sonic the Hedgehog's adventures are now available in the popular digest format -- but that's just not enough Sonic for all you hungry Sonic fans out there! By popular demand, get ready for a SUPER-SIZED issue filled with even more Sonic the Hedgehog goodness, stretching back to the beginning of the comics' 20 year history! Blast through to your digital comic store at SONIC SPEED to find out the origins of everyone's favorite blue hedgehog! Can Sonic and the heroic Freedom Fighters save the world from the evils of Dr. Robtnik? Discover all the thrills, chills and spills for yourself with classic Sonic comics as only Sonic Super Digest can provide!
The mystery behind Rene and Carol is brought to light. Also, the cast must defend themselves against an angry foe.

Damon Salvatore has returned from the war, and battle has taken its toll. He’s desperately ill, but Katherine’s more interested in scoring points against a rival for his affections than worrying about his interests.
name: Laces Part 2 of 3

description: It's time for the student-faculty bowling night! It's teachers vs. students and, while the teachers may be older and have plenty of years of bowling experience on their side, some changes to the game might lean in the kids' favor! Find out who gets the most strikes in "For Whom the Bowl Tolls!"
name: For Whom the Bowls Tolls

person_credits.role: writer, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover
